
VSCODE
1. install git extension
https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=forevolve.git-extensions-for-vs-code

1.1 press Ctrl+ P
1.2 ext install forevolve.git-extensions-for-vs-code

2. install git exclude
https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=boukichi.git-exclude

3.click Source Control on Left pane
  Select Changes Tab
  press + for Stage change
  press F1 , Git:Commit
  press F1 , Git:Push /  Select Commits Tab, then select top Arrow, Push


A new repo from an existing project
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Say you’ve got an existing project that you want to start tracking with git.

Go to github.
Log in to your account.
Click the new repository button in the top-right. You’ll have an option there to initialize the repository with a README file, but I don’t.
Click the “Create repository” button.

Go into the directory containing the project.
git init
git add README.md
git commit -m "first commit"
git branch -M master
git remote add origin https://github.com/shwang1a/test3.git
git push -u origin master


Git others commands
----------------------------------------
git clone https://github.com/shwang1a/OpenAPI.git
git config --global core.editor "gedit -w"
git remote set-url origin https://<<username>>：<<password>>@github.com/shwang1a/OpenAPI.git
git remote -v

git add filename	#stage change
git commit
git push

